-- Gold slides 2 percent on stock losses
-- 
-- Fri Mar 2, 2007 9:02am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/03/02/us-markets-gold-fall-idUSL0253729520070302

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Gold was hit by further selling on Friday as investors continued to reduce their exposure to the metal after heavy losses in stock markets this week. 


 Spot gold fell over 2 percent to $648.50 an ounce by 8:30 a.m. ET, its lowest since Feb. 8 and compared with a late quote in New York of $662.60/663.30.